<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 21 at 8:05PM MDT until July 21 at 8:30PM MDT by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 830 PM MDT
FOR CENTRAL WELD COUNTY...
At 805 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles southeast of
Gill, or 14 miles east of Greeley, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees. Hail damage to
vehicles is expected.
Locations impacted include...
Riverside Reservoir.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
